WEBVTT

00:01.268 --> 00:02.501
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

00:48.415 --> 00:50.482
Check, check and checkmate.

00:52.552 --> 00:54.786
(SPEAKING ROBOTICALLY)

00:54.821 --> 00:56.789
<i>Grodd, Gorilla. Negative.</i>

01:00.293 --> 01:02.928
<i>Luthor, Lex. Positive match.</i>

01:06.466 --> 01:09.768
LEX: This better be good.
I'm playing myself.
And winning!

01:13.807 --> 01:15.740
ROBOT: <i> You will come with me.</i>

01:15.775 --> 01:18.443
Well, since you asked
so nicely...

01:18.478 --> 01:19.978
I'm intrigued.

01:22.983 --> 01:24.483
(LASERS FIRING)

01:28.355 --> 01:30.822
MICHAEL: <i> That's how</i>
<i>Luthor escaped.</i>

01:30.857 --> 01:34.126
This the third abduction
in 24 hours. Same MO.

01:34.161 --> 01:36.995
It also made off with
the Brain and the Calculator.

01:39.866 --> 01:43.301
-LEX: <i> Hey what are you... No!</i>
-Why? What's the connection?

01:43.336 --> 01:45.337
Each is brilliant
in his own right.

01:45.372 --> 01:48.840
Maybe Darkseid stumbled across
a really tough sudoku.

01:48.875 --> 01:50.408
I don't know.

01:50.443 --> 01:53.078
As the third smartest person
in the world,

01:53.113 --> 01:54.980
I hoped you'd be more helpful.

01:55.015 --> 01:57.182
Conjecture without
data is guessing.

01:57.217 --> 02:00.819
And as for those world's
smartest lists, they're
never accurate.

02:00.854 --> 02:03.655
-(ALARM BUZZING)
-Saved by the bell.

02:03.690 --> 02:04.823
It's time to T-up.

02:08.562 --> 02:12.998
<i>Batman, Mr. Terrific,</i>
<i>positive match.</i>
<i>You will come with me.</i>

02:17.170 --> 02:20.172
BATMAN: It's trying to capture
us as well.

02:20.207 --> 02:22.007
-(LASERS FIRING)
-Only one way to find out.

02:24.878 --> 02:26.945
Looks like I was right again.

02:26.980 --> 02:29.614
CALCULATOR: Yeah, well even a
broken clock is right
twice a day.

02:29.649 --> 02:33.185
<i>Ooh, good one, meat-sack.</i>

02:33.220 --> 02:35.420
-Least I can do this.
-(BLOWING RASPBERRIES)

02:37.390 --> 02:40.192
LEX: Enough!
Could this gathering
get any worse?

02:43.196 --> 02:45.063
I spoke too soon.

02:45.098 --> 02:48.633
Someone took great
lengths to get us all here.
But why?

02:48.668 --> 02:54.506
<i>I suspected</i>
<i>it had to do with IQ's</i>
<i>until you two showed up.</i>

02:54.541 --> 02:57.642
VOICE: <i> IQ has everything</i>
<i>to do with it.</i>

02:57.677 --> 03:00.345
<i>As five of the most</i>
<i>brilliant minds on Earth,</i>

03:00.380 --> 03:04.015
<i>you have been selected</i>
<i>to compete in my brain games.</i>

03:04.050 --> 03:08.086
(SCOFFS) Lex Luthor
doesn't lower himself
to compete with rabble.

03:08.121 --> 03:10.722
VOICE: <i> I've prepared</i>
<i>a series of competitions,</i>

03:10.757 --> 03:14.192
<i>devised to test your</i>
<i>intellectual limitations.</i>

03:14.227 --> 03:17.696
<i>Only the most brilliant of you</i>
<i>will survive to win the prize.</i>

03:17.731 --> 03:18.897
And if we don't play along?

03:18.932 --> 03:22.200
<i>Simple, you'll be obliterated.</i>

03:22.235 --> 03:26.004
<i>So, participating</i>
<i>is a no-brainer.</i>

03:26.039 --> 03:29.040
Hope the challenges will be
smarter than your jokes.

03:29.075 --> 03:31.310
<i>Enough impertinence.</i>
<i>We begin.</i>

03:35.148 --> 03:37.282
<i>Let's start with</i>
<i>something remedial.</i>

03:37.951 --> 03:40.418
<i>A race.</i>

03:40.453 --> 03:44.456
THE BRAIN: <i> There are</i>
<i>no pedals. How do you</i>
<i>expect us to race?</i>

03:44.491 --> 03:47.926
VOICE: <i> I'll give you fuel,</i>
<i>for your mind.</i>

03:47.961 --> 03:52.631
<i>On each of your dashboards,</i>
<i>is a sphere</i>
<i>with colored lights.</i>

03:52.666 --> 03:56.235
<i>Arrange those into a shape</i>
<i>that's optically pleasing.</i>

03:57.337 --> 03:58.637
<i>And you're ready to roll.</i>

04:00.974 --> 04:02.674
(BEEPING)

04:22.362 --> 04:23.795
VOICE: <i> Well done.</i>

04:23.830 --> 04:26.131
<i>You're all as smart</i>
<i>as I'd hoped.</i>

04:26.166 --> 04:28.266
<i>I'm certain you've all</i>
<i>also ascertained</i>

04:28.301 --> 04:30.635
<i>that the last one</i>
<i>to cross the finish line</i>

04:30.670 --> 04:32.604
<i>will be eliminated.</i>

04:38.511 --> 04:40.178
Time to go into overdrive.

04:43.850 --> 04:45.651
(BEAM FIRING)

04:47.520 --> 04:48.720
I'll get him.

04:58.998 --> 05:02.334
CALCULATOR: Out of my way,
jar head. I think you're past
your sell date.

05:02.369 --> 05:03.635
THE BRAIN: <i> Neanderthal.</i>

05:05.739 --> 05:06.872
(SCREAMS)

05:17.484 --> 05:18.483
(SCREAMS)

05:24.324 --> 05:25.424
(SCREAMS)

05:27.026 --> 05:28.193
(GRUNTS)

05:30.397 --> 05:32.964
What?

05:32.999 --> 05:35.500
You know what I'm thinking?
That yee-haw strategy.

05:35.535 --> 05:37.235
What's the relative
gravity on this planet?

05:40.240 --> 05:44.743
THE BRAIN: <i> Looks as if you'll</i>
<i>be eliminated first, Batman,</i>
<i>and good riddance.</i>

05:44.778 --> 05:47.746
He said last to finish.
He didn't say
it had to be in a car.

05:51.618 --> 05:54.052
Okay, then, T-minus
three, two...

05:55.688 --> 05:57.622
MR. TERRIFIC: Yee-haw!

05:58.858 --> 06:00.625
What? Impossible!

06:03.630 --> 06:05.230
(LASER FIRING)

06:05.265 --> 06:06.264
(SCREAMS)

06:12.372 --> 06:14.939
THE BRAIN: <i> Robbed.</i>
<i>I was robbed!</i>

06:14.974 --> 06:16.475
Shocking, but not lethal.

06:17.210 --> 06:18.777
(VOICE LAUGHS)

06:18.812 --> 06:21.079
VOICE: <i> Not yet.</i>
<i>It's only fair that losers</i>

06:21.114 --> 06:22.781
<i>first suffer a period</i>
<i>of humiliation.</i>

06:28.955 --> 06:30.755
Enough gloating.

06:30.790 --> 06:32.924
Get to the second test.

06:32.959 --> 06:36.528
VOICE: <i> Seems our third</i>
<i>place winner is anxious</i>
<i>to prove his worth.</i>

06:36.563 --> 06:38.063
<i>-Fine.</i>
-(THUNDER CRACKLES)

06:41.801 --> 06:43.935
<i>Let's accelerate</i>
<i>the process then.</i>

06:43.970 --> 06:46.704
<i>The first two who make it</i>
<i>to the red platforms win.</i>

06:46.739 --> 06:48.239
<i>The two who don't,</i>

06:48.274 --> 06:49.274
<i>lose.</i>

06:58.351 --> 07:00.252
What is this? A trick?

07:03.189 --> 07:04.656
Ha! It's there.

07:09.095 --> 07:10.762
They're moving in a pattern.

07:10.797 --> 07:11.863
I see it.

07:14.534 --> 07:16.835
-CALCULATOR: Not this time,
Dark Knight.
-(LASER FIRING)

07:16.870 --> 07:17.869
Ah!

07:19.973 --> 07:21.840
(CALCULATOR GRUNTS, SCREAMS)

07:26.679 --> 07:27.813
Aw!

07:34.521 --> 07:36.021
-(LASER FIRING)
-(GRUNTS)

07:40.360 --> 07:41.626
Game over.

07:42.362 --> 07:44.095
(GRUNTS)

07:44.130 --> 07:45.831
Turned about
is fair play, Luthor.

07:48.201 --> 07:50.602
And I'm all about fair play.

07:50.637 --> 07:53.038
VOICE: <i> Hurry now.</i>
<i>Only one of you can win.</i>

07:54.374 --> 07:56.007
Terrific, no!

07:56.042 --> 07:58.143
-(LASERS FIRING)
-VOICE: <i> Disqualified!</i>

08:04.417 --> 08:08.853
Ha! The world's third
smartest man just
outsmarted himself.

08:08.888 --> 08:12.357
VOICE: <i> We have our finalists.</i>
<i>On to our final round.</i>

08:21.200 --> 08:22.534
Chess!

08:22.569 --> 08:25.069
Oh, Batman, I haven't
lost a chess match in...

08:25.104 --> 08:27.405
Well, come to think of it.
I've never lost one.

08:32.612 --> 08:34.546
(LASERS FIRING)

08:34.581 --> 08:37.916
VOICE: <i> For every second</i>
<i>you take to move,</i>
<i>my drone fires a shot.</i>

08:40.019 --> 08:42.087
<i>So much more effective</i>
<i>than a chess clock.</i>

08:44.791 --> 08:46.558
Okay, sphere, let's unmask.

08:48.595 --> 08:50.929
Now hack this baby
nice and quiet-like.

08:54.801 --> 08:56.401
(LASERS FIRING)

08:56.436 --> 08:58.069
Check. (GRUNTS)

08:58.104 --> 08:59.404
Pardon me.

09:01.474 --> 09:03.207
That's cheating.

09:03.242 --> 09:05.877
A win is still a win.
Check mate.

09:05.912 --> 09:06.945
(GRUNTS)

09:10.617 --> 09:13.084
VOICE: <i> Congratulations,</i>
<i>Lex Luthor.</i>

09:13.119 --> 09:15.753
<i>Your ingenuity and</i>
<i>resourcefulness</i>
<i>have won the day.</i>

09:15.788 --> 09:18.256
<i>You are the smartest</i>
<i>of the smart.</i>

09:18.291 --> 09:20.391
I could've told you that.

09:20.426 --> 09:22.460
VOICE: <i> Now, you get</i>
<i>your prize.</i>

09:23.396 --> 09:24.563
(RUMBLING)

09:27.500 --> 09:29.467
What is this? Release me!

09:34.974 --> 09:36.708
Mr. Mind.

09:36.743 --> 09:39.611
I should've smelled your tiny
slug trail from the start.

09:39.646 --> 09:44.082
<i>You see? I have always</i>
<i>been underestimated</i>
<i>because of my size.</i>

09:44.117 --> 09:47.785
<i>But now, my presence will be</i>
<i>as big as my greatness.</i>

09:47.820 --> 09:50.888
(SCREAMS)

09:50.923 --> 09:55.460
<i>With these helmets,</i>
<i>I'll install my powerful brain</i>
<i>into your full-sized body.</i>

09:55.495 --> 09:57.996
<i>I'll have your</i>
<i>added IQ as a bonus.</i>

10:00.700 --> 10:01.766
(SCREAMS)

10:04.303 --> 10:05.837
<i>-Huh?</i>
-(SIGHS)

10:06.639 --> 10:08.139
<i>Terrific.</i>

10:08.174 --> 10:10.475
Hate to break up
to this meeting of the minds.

10:10.510 --> 10:11.643
<i>Destroy him!</i>

10:14.213 --> 10:16.848
See once I hacked your system,
I did what anyone would do.

10:19.819 --> 10:21.619
(ELECTRICAL BUZZING)

10:21.654 --> 10:23.688
-(THUDS)
-MR. TERRIFIC: I freed Batman.

10:24.957 --> 10:26.057
(WHIMPERS)

10:28.494 --> 10:30.795
What? You were toying with me?

10:30.830 --> 10:33.431
You are a pawn
I sacrificed, Luthor.

10:33.466 --> 10:37.001
I knew Terrific had a plan.
Even if I didn't know
what it was.

10:37.036 --> 10:42.006
Obviously, he wouldn't
try to win the brain games.
First prize was destruction.

10:42.041 --> 10:46.310
<i>You surprise me, Mr. Terrific.</i>
<i>I didn't expect you</i>
<i>to be victorious.</i>

10:46.345 --> 10:50.882
<i>After all, you're only</i>
<i>the third on the</i>
<i>smartest person list.</i>

10:50.917 --> 10:53.918
Well, I prefer not to draw
too much attention to myself.

10:55.054 --> 10:56.688
Who do you think
wrote that list?

11:00.560 --> 11:03.428
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
